Project Overview
This project is a Student Result Management System developed using Java.
It allows users to manage student records and automatically calculate results such as total marks, average, and grade.

The system is menu-driven and simulates a real-world student record management application where data is processed dynamically using object-oriented programming.

Objectives
Understand Java OOP concepts
Manage student records using ArrayList
Perform result calculations (total, average, grade)
Build a menu-driven application
Implement CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete)

Tools & Technologies
Java
JDK 8 or above
VS Code / Eclipse / IntelliJ

Modules Used
java.util.ArrayList → for storing student records
java.util.Scanner → for user input

Project Description

The application manages student details including:

Roll Number
Name
Marks (5 subjects)

The system processes this data and provides:

Total marks calculation
Average calculation
Grade assignment
Record management operations

The program is menu-driven, allowing users to interact and perform different operations easily.

Key Concepts Used
Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
Classes and Objects
ArrayList
Arrays
Loops (for, while)
Conditional statements (if-else)

Algorithm

Start the program
Display menu
Read user choice

Perform operation:

Add student
Display students
Search student
Update student
Delete student

Calculate total, average, and grade
Display result
Repeat until user exits

Features
Add student records
Display all students
Search by roll number
Update marks
Delete records
Automatic result calculation
Simple menu-driven interface
Beginner-friendly design

Result
The system successfully manages student records and performs accurate result calculations including total, average, and grade.

Conclusion
This project demonstrates how Java can be used to build a simple student management system using object-oriented programming.
It provides practical knowledge of handling data, performing calculations, and designing menu-driven applications.
